      "content": "yeah that makes sense. but looking back, do you think the movement actually achieved its goals, or was the nonviolent approach the only thing that really worked to fix the system? like, do historians generally agree that those more \"confrontational\" groups were actually useful, or were they just seen as a distraction?",
